# Named effect callbacks

Pass a **named function** as the first argument to `useEffect` and `useLayoutEffect` (same style as `function syncTabFromUrl()` in `useLayoutEffect`).

- Makes React DevTools and stack traces name the effect.
- Makes the file grep-friendly (`function scheduleFoo`).

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid
useEffect(() => {
  if (!open) return
  const t = setTimeout(onClose, 300)
  return () => clearTimeout(t)
}, [open, onClose])

// ✅ Prefer
useEffect(
  function scheduleCloseWhenOpen() {
    if (!open) return
    const t = setTimeout(onClose, 300)
    return () => clearTimeout(t)
  },
  [open, onClose],
)
```
